cs.CV, cs.SD, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.MM

The paper deals with lipreading, which is a task related to computer vision (CV) and speech recognition (SD). Therefore, cs.CV and cs.SD are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also uses deep learning techniques, which are commonly used in natural language processing (NLP) and computer vision (CV) tasks, such as image and speech recognition. Hence, cs.CL and cs.LG are also likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with multi-view lipreading, which involves processing multiple images or videos, making cs.MM a possible sub-category as well.
